      "text": "Theme Auto Light Dark |"
    },
    {
      "chunkId": "ck_code_001_py_asyncio_0001",
      "headingPath": [
        "asyncio — Asynchronous I/O ¶"
      ],
      "order": 9,
      "pageId": "code_001_py_asyncio",
      "paragraphId": "pg_code_001_py_asyncio_0010",
      "sourceBlockType": "code",
      "text": "import asyncio async def main (): print ( 'Hello ...' ) await asyncio . sleep ( 1 ) print ( '... World!' ) asyncio . run ( main ())"
    },
    {
      "chunkId": "ck_code_001_py_asyncio_0001",
      "headingPath": [
        "asyncio — Asynchronous I/O ¶"
      ],
      "order": 10,
      "pageId": "code_001_py_asyncio",
      "paragraphId": "pg_code_001_py_asyncio_0011",
      "sourceBlockType": "paragraph",
      "text": "asyncio is a library to write concurrent code using the async/await syntax."
    },
    {
      "chunkId": "ck_code_001_py_asyncio_0001",
      "headingPath": [
        "asyncio — Asynchronous I/O ¶"
      ],
      "order": 11,
      "pageId": "code_001_py_asyncio",
      "paragraphId": "pg_code_001_py_asyncio_0012",
      "sourceBlockType": "paragraph",
      "text": "asyncio is used as a foundation for multiple Python asynchronous frameworks that provide high-performance network and web-servers, database connection libraries, distributed task queues, etc."
    },
    {
      "chunkId": "ck_code_001_py_asyncio_0001",
      "headingPath": [
        "asyncio — Asynchronous I/O ¶"
      ],
      "order": 12,
      "pageId": "code_001_py_asyncio",
      "paragraphId": "pg_code_001_py_asyncio_0013",
      "sourceBlockType": "paragraph",
      "text": "asyncio is often a perfect fit for IO-bound and high-level structured network code."
    },
    {
      "chunkId": "ck_code_001_py_asyncio_0001",
      "headingPath": [
        "asyncio — Asynchronous I/O ¶"
      ],
      "order": 13,
      "pageId": "code_001_py_asyncio",
      "paragraphId": "pg_code_001_py_asyncio_0014",
      "sourceBlockType": "paragraph",
      "text": "Explanation of the fundamentals of asyncio."
    },
    {
      "chunkId": "ck_code_001_py_asyncio_0001",
      "headingPath": [
        "asyncio — Asynchronous I/O ¶"
      ],
      "order": 14,
      "pageId": "code_001_py_asyncio",
      "paragraphId": "pg_code_001_py_asyncio_0015",
      "sourceBlockType": "paragraph",
      "text": "asyncio provides a set of high-level APIs to:"
    },
    {
      "chunkId": "ck_code_001_py_asyncio_0001",
      "headingPath": [
        "asyncio — Asynchronous I/O ¶"
      ],
      "order": 15,
      "pageId": "code_001_py_asyncio",
      "paragraphId": "pg_code_001_py_asyncio_0016",
      "sourceBlockType": "paragraph",
      "text": "run Python coroutines concurrently and have full control over their execution;"
    },
    {
      "chunkId": "ck_code_001_py_asyncio_0001",
      "headingPath": [
        "asyncio — Asynchronous I/O ¶"
      ],
      "order": 16,
      "pageId": "code_001_py_asyncio",
      "paragraphId": "pg_code_001_py_asyncio_0017",
      "sourceBlockType": "paragraph",
      "text": "perform network IO and IPC ;"
    },
    {
      "chunkId": "ck_code_001_py_asyncio_0001",
      "headingPath": [
        "asyncio — Asynchronous I/O ¶"
      ],
      "order": 17,
      "pageId": "code_001_py_asyncio",
      "paragraphId": "pg_code_001_py_asyncio_0018",
      "sourceBlockType": "paragraph",
      "text": "control subprocesses ;"
    },
    {
      "chunkId": "ck_code_001_py_asyncio_0001",
      "headingPath": [
        "asyncio — Asynchronous I/O ¶"
      ],
      "order": 18,
      "pageId": "code_001_py_asyncio",
      "paragraphId": "pg_code_001_py_asyncio_0019",
      "sourceBlockType": "paragraph",
      "text": "distribute tasks via queues ;"
    },
    {
      "chunkId": "ck_code_001_py_asyncio_0001",
      "headingPath": [
        "asyncio — Asynchronous I/O ¶"
      ],
      "order": 19,
      "pageId": "code_001_py_asyncio",
      "paragraphId": "pg_code_001_py_asyncio_0020",
      "sourceBlockType": "paragraph",
      "text": "synchronize concurrent code;"
    },
    {
      "chunkId": "ck_code_001_py_asyncio_0001",
      "headingPath": [
        "asyncio — Asynchronous I/O ¶"
      ],
      "order": 20,
      "pageId": "code_001_py_asyncio",
      "paragraphId": "pg_code_001_py_asyncio_0021",
      "sourceBlockType": "paragraph",
      "text": "Additionally, there are low-level APIs for library and framework developers to:"
    },
    {
      "chunkId": "ck_code_001_py_asyncio_0001",
      "headingPath": [
        "asyncio — Asynchronous I/O ¶"
      ],
      "order": 21,
      "pageId": "code_001_py_asyncio",
      "paragraphId": "pg_code_001_py_asyncio_0022",
      "sourceBlockType": "paragraph",
      "text": "create and manage event loops , which provide asynchronous APIs for networking , running subprocesses , handling OS signals , etc;"
    },
    {
      "chunkId": "ck_code_001_py_asyncio_0001",
      "headingPath": [
        "asyncio — Asynchronous I/O ¶"
      ],
      "order": 22,
      "pageId": "code_001_py_asyncio",
      "paragraphId": "pg_code_001_py_asyncio_0023",
      "sourceBlockType": "paragraph",
      "text": "implement efficient protocols using transports ;"
    },
    {
      "chunkId": "ck_code_001_py_asyncio_0001",
      "headingPath": [
        "asyncio — Asynchronous I/O ¶"
      ],
      "order": 23,
      "pageId": "code_001_py_asyncio",
      "paragraphId": "pg_code_001_py_asyncio_0024",
      "sourceBlockType": "paragraph",
      "text": "bridge callback-based libraries and code with async/await syntax."
    },
    {
      "chunkId": "ck_code_001_py_asyncio_0001",
      "headingPath": [
        "asyncio — Asynchronous I/O ¶"
      ],
      "order": 24,
      "pageId": "code_001_py_asyncio",
      "paragraphId": "pg_code_001_py_asyncio_0025",
      "sourceBlockType": "paragraph",
      "text": "Availability : not WASI."
    },
    {
      "chunkId": "ck_code_001_py_asyncio_0002",
      "headingPath": [
        "asyncio — Asynchronous I/O ¶"
      ],
      "order": 25,
      "pageId": "code_001_py_asyncio",
      "paragraphId": "pg_code_001_py_asyncio_0026",
      "sourceBlockType": "paragraph",
      "text": "This module does not work or is not available on WebAssembly. See WebAssembly platforms for more information."
    },
    {
      "chunkId": "ck_code_001_py_asyncio_0002",
      "headingPath": [
        "asyncio — Asynchronous I/O ¶"
      ],
      "order": 26,
      "pageId": "code_001_py_asyncio",
      "paragraphId": "pg_code_001_py_asyncio_0027",
      "sourceBlockType": "paragraph",
      "text": "You can experiment with an asyncio concurrent context in the REPL :"
    },
    {
      "chunkId": "ck_code_001_py_asyncio_0002",
      "headingPath": [
        "asyncio — Asynchronous I/O ¶"
      ],
      "order": 27,
      "pageId": "code_001_py_asyncio",
      "paragraphId": "pg_code_001_py_asyncio_0028",
      "sourceBlockType": "code",
      "text": "$ python -m asyncio asyncio REPL ... Use \"await\" directly instead of \"asyncio.run()\". Type \"help\", \"copyright\", \"credits\" or \"license\" for more information. >>> import asyncio >>> await asyncio . sleep ( 10 , result = 'hello' ) 'hello'"
    },
    {
      "chunkId": "ck_code_001_py_asyncio_0002",
      "headingPath": [
        "asyncio — Asynchronous I/O ¶"
      ],
      "order": 28,
      "pageId": "code_001_py_asyncio",
      "paragraphId": "pg_code_001_py_asyncio_0029",
      "sourceBlockType": "paragraph",
      "text": "This REPL provides limited compatibility with PYTHON_BASIC_REPL . It is recommended that the default REPL is used for full functionality and the latest features."
    },
    {
      "chunkId": "ck_code_001_py_asyncio_0002",
      "headingPath": [
        "asyncio — Asynchronous I/O ¶"
      ],
      "order": 29,
      "pageId": "code_001_py_asyncio",
      "paragraphId": "pg_code_001_py_asyncio_0030",
      "sourceBlockType": "paragraph",
      "text": "Raises an auditing event cpython.run_stdin with no arguments."
    },
    {
      "chunkId": "ck_code_001_py_asyncio_0002",
      "headingPath": [
        "asyncio — Asynchronous I/O ¶"
      ],
      "order": 30,
      "pageId": "code_001_py_asyncio",
      "paragraphId": "pg_code_001_py_asyncio_0031",
      "sourceBlockType": "paragraph",
      "text": "Changed in version 3.12.5: (also 3.11.10, 3.10.15, 3.9.20, and 3.8.20) Emits audit events."
    },
    {
      "chunkId": "ck_code_001_py_asyncio_0002",
      "headingPath": [
        "asyncio — Asynchronous I/O ¶"
      ],
      "order": 31,
      "pageId": "code_001_py_asyncio",
      "paragraphId": "pg_code_001_py_asyncio_0032",
      "sourceBlockType": "paragraph",
      "text": "Changed in version 3.13: Uses PyREPL if possible, in which case PYTHONSTARTUP is also executed. Emits audit events."
    },
    {
      "chunkId": "ck_code_001_py_asyncio_0002",
      "headingPath": [
        "asyncio — Asynchronous I/O ¶"
      ],
      "order": 32,
      "pageId": "code_001_py_asyncio",
